All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
BehaviourMode
When you initialize WeatherSDK in the first time you have to provide a Behaviour mode you want to use.
ON_DEMAND - useful if you desire to get data from the API only once.
POLLING - useful if you need to get data from the API several times automatically during the specified time.
CachedData
This class represents all data that have been cached.
It has max cache capacity of 10.
CachedWeatherData
This class describes weather data that have been cached.
CityCoordinates
This class contains data about city coordinates providing name of city, latitude and longitude.
GeocodingAPI
The GeocodingAPI is required to collect coordinates for the WeatherOfCityAPI.
GeocodingApiCoordinatesAreNullException
 
RestQuery
This is a simple RestQueryBuilder.
RestQuery.Builder
 
RestQueryExecuter
RestQueryExecuter is a class provides Rest Template interface to work with and also checks if response has any mistakes.
RestQueryExecuterResponseIsNullException
 
RestQueryExecutorServerReturnedAnException
 
RestQueryExecutorTooManyQueriesException
 
RestQueryExecutorWrongApiKeyException
 
RestQueryExecutorWrongCityNameException
 
ServiceType
ServiceType points what API is used when RestTemplateExecuter is called to work with response codes.
WeatherClient
WeatherClient is a main class which uses all methods together to transform your city's name to the meaningful information.
It also contains methods to handle with POLLING and Cached Data.
WeatherClientApiKeyDuplicatedException
 
WeatherClientApiKeyHasNotBeenFoundException
 
WeatherOfCityAPI
The WeatherOfCityAPI uses coordinates from the GeocodingAPI to grab a fresh data for city you provide.
WeatherOfCityResponseIsInvalidException
 
WeatherSDKClientHandler
This is a basic class to initialize the WeatherSDK.
It checks a Map of records of API_KEYS that you provide to manage with several instances.
Use instances to set up multiple profiles to handle with.

You have to use static getInstance() method to start work with the WeatherSDK.
